#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:2
#: 7dc8499de6f74a82b48631ab7a47b9eb
msgid "Plasticity Strip (J2 with Isotropic Hardening)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:4
#: aeb2a788c590416fa52c673a52629007
msgid ""
"A 2D plane-strain plasticity problem: a :math:`1.0 \\times 0.2` m steel "
"strip is stretched 10 % then unloaded, exhibiting the characteristic "
"permanent (plastic) deformation that the elastic solver in "
":doc:`cantilever_beam` cannot capture. The script "
"``examples/solid/plasticity_strip/plasticity_strip.py`` uses J2 flow "
"theory with linear isotropic hardening, integrated in a **variational "
"constitutive update** style — the constitutive response is encoded as an "
"algorithmic potential, the displacement update is one L-BFGS pass, and "
"history variables are advanced once per converged step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:17
#: 3911a971e3fe4b9cb1c52a5c569be00a
msgid "Problem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:19
#: 64e97f1e2a134ea68dda4a1ad3d97490
msgid ""
"Small-strain elastoplasticity. The Cauchy stress is the elastic response "
"of the **elastic** part of the strain:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:22
#: 0771a844d6e54248afca7e8d835df56f
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"\\boldsymbol{\\sigma} \\;=\\;\n"
"\\mathbb{C} : (\\boldsymbol{\\varepsilon} - \\boldsymbol{\\varepsilon}^p),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:27
#: bbcf8fc676c9489a89ab06ddf34280c8
msgid "with yield surface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:29
#: 701795cd7f844d82a93581644f60358b
msgid ""
"f(\\boldsymbol{\\sigma}, \\alpha)\n"
"\\;=\\;\n"
"\\|\\,\\mathrm{dev}\\, \\boldsymbol{\\sigma}\\,\\|\n"
"- \\sqrt{\\tfrac{2}{3}} \\bigl(\\sigma_y + H\\, \\alpha\\bigr),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:36
#: 6e8488afacdd48f29b916f138539f1bb
msgid ""
"evolution :math:`\\dot{\\boldsymbol{\\varepsilon}}^p = \\dot\\gamma\\, "
"\\mathbf{n}`, :math:`\\dot\\alpha = \\sqrt{\\tfrac{2}{3}}\\, "
"\\dot\\gamma`. Material: :math:`E = 200` GPa, :math:`\\nu = 0.3`, "
":math:`\\sigma_y = 250` MPa, :math:`H = 1` GPa."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:41
#: 7d5c09ee493240829b8488febbd521a4
msgid "Boundary conditions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:43
#: 2f87938901b74392b19e12cb199d5263
msgid ":math:`x = 0`: roller (:math:`u_x = 0`),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:44
#: c6fff7d5cddb4f09922e9ea819360049
msgid "corner :math:`(0, 0)`: full pin (:math:`u_x = u_y = 0`),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:45
#: 5f9222d832a64396a7d73bdc983a8e11
msgid ""
":math:`x = 1`: prescribed :math:`u_x` ramped from 0 to 0.10 m (10 steps),"
" then back down to 0 (10 more steps)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:50
#: 797f55a6ca234ccd978ca35ba2f827a3
msgid "Variational constitutive update"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:52
#: fcb44d6ca7a043ecae642913a2d1b9ad
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Rather than implementing an explicit \"radial return\" map per quadrature"
" point, the script defines an **algorithmic potential** "
":math:`\\Pi^\\text{alg}(\\boldsymbol{\\varepsilon}, "
"\\boldsymbol{\\varepsilon}^p_n, \\alpha_n)` whose stationarity in the "
"plastic variables recovers the standard return-mapping equations. The "
"displacement update at each step is then a single minimization of the "
"integrated potential:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:60
#: 94267683f45d4cfdbae431f1ffaf9239
msgid ""
"\\mathbf{u}^{n+1}\n"
"\\;=\\;\n"
"\\arg\\min_{\\mathbf{u}}\n"
"\\int_\\Omega "
"\\Pi^\\text{alg}\\bigl(\\boldsymbol{\\varepsilon}(\\mathbf{u}),\\,\n"
"\\boldsymbol{\\varepsilon}^p_n,\\, \\alpha_n\\bigr)\n"
"\\,\\mathrm{d}\\Omega,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:69
#: 28505285491c44bfaffff88a48b96f37
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"with autograd providing both the gradient (residual) and, via L-BFGS' "
"implicit Hessian approximation, an effective tangent. After convergence, "
"the history variables :math:`(\\boldsymbol{\\varepsilon}^p, \\alpha)` are"
" advanced once to the new converged values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:75
#: a709fe35dcdc496cb745192bcb042c5d
msgid ""
"The potential is implemented in "
":class:`~tensormesh.assemble.J2Plasticity`, a built-in shipping in "
":mod:`tensormesh.assemble`. From the user's side it looks like any other "
"custom assembler:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:80
#: 75d7722bf4504b30aba7b052e54f505f
msgid "examples/solid/plasticity_strip/plasticity_strip.py (essence)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:116
#: ff45c7cd9b4f48b8824b5d81a4be958d
msgid "History variables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:118
#: 72a32edb1c7a465baa3dd982199d55f3
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The plastic strain tensor :math:`\\boldsymbol{\\varepsilon}^p` and the "
"equivalent plastic strain :math:`\\alpha` are stored **per-element / per-"
"quadrature-point**, accessed through ``model.history``. They are passed "
"into the closure as ``element_data`` (per-quadrature, per-element "
"tensors), which TensorMesh dispatches as kwargs to the underlying "
"``forward`` method exactly the same way ``point_data`` is dispatched (see"
" :doc:`../../user_guide/forms`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/solid/plasticity_strip.rst:127
#: 3faa13605e0d4d5d9f35c482f73de621
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"After each load step's L-BFGS converges, the script calls "
"``model.advance_history(u_active)`` which evaluates the converged "
":math:`\\boldsymbol{\\varepsilon}^p, \\alpha` from the current "
"displacement and overwrites the stored history."
msgstr ""

